Proposed extension of then line 19 from Piazzale Gambara. Works began on June 2nd 1943 but were halted in August and never resumed. The project would be abandoned after the war, and spare parts for it were used for repairs on the damaged network.
This loop was built in 1957 to replace the old terminus in Piazzale Amendola, as it was obstructed by the construction of the metro. It was used by special services to the fair (line 50).
